HEADWORD: Ironbound
<hw>I"ron*bound`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Bound
as with iron; rugged; <as>as, an <ex>ironbound</ex>
coast</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Rigid; unyielding; <as>as, <ex>ironbound</ex>
traditions</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Iron-cased</ent>⟦br⟧
